text: Kurt Liander (28 January 1932 – 10 March 2020) was a Swedish footballer and football manager. He played mostly for AIK and IFK Stockholm. He played 5 times for the Swedish national team. He also had a career as a manager. Liander died on 10 March 2020 in Stockholm at the age of 88.AIK Fotboll sörjer Kurt Liander ==References== ==Other websites== *Profile Category:1932 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Footballers from Stockholm Category:Swedish football managers
